{"id":4574,"date":"2025-01-16T18:44:18","date_gmt":"2025-01-16T18:44:18","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/?post_type=wiki&#038;p=4574"},"modified":"2025-01-16T18:50:35","modified_gmt":"2025-01-16T18:50:35","slug":"deep-sea-scale","status":"publish","type":"wiki","link":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/items\/evolution-items\/deep-sea-scale\/","title":{"rendered":"Deep Sea Scale"},"content":{"rendered":"<div class=\"table-wrap\">\n<table class=\"table grey left\" style=\"min-width:340px;\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th colspan=\"3\" class=\"text-large center\">Locations<\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>#<\/th>\n<th>Method<\/th>\n<th>Repeatable<\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<\/thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th><strong>1<\/strong><\/th>\n<td><strong>Route 3<\/strong> &#8211; Hidden in the small piece of land east from the shore (requires Surf)<\/td>\n<td>No<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th><strong>2<\/strong><\/th>\n<td><strong>Battle Frontier<\/strong> &#8211; Exchange for 32 Battle Points (BP) at the Exchange Service Counter (eastern side of building)<\/td>\n<td>Yes<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th><strong>3<\/strong><\/th>\n<td>\n        <strong>Wild Held Item<\/strong> &#8211; Held by the following wild Pokemon:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/pokemon\/chinchou\/\">Chinchou<\/a> (5% chance)<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/pokemon\/lanturn\/\">Lanturn<\/a> (5% chance)<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/pokemon\/basculin\/\">Basculin<\/a> (Blue-Striped, 5% chance)<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/pokemon\/relicanth\/\">Relicanth<\/a> (5% chance)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/td>\n<td>Yes<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<\/div>\n<p>The easiest way of acquiring a Deep Sea Scale in Pokemon Unbound is by collecting it from Route 3. You can do this as soon as you obtain HM03 Surf as this is required to reach the area containing the Deep Sea Scale.<\/p>\n<p>Alternatively, you can also obtain Deep Sea Scales by catching wild Chinchou and Lanturn as these Pokemon have a 5% chance of holding the item. Deep Sea Scales can also be exchanged at the Battle Frontier for 32 Battle Points.<\/p>\n<h2>Once-only Methods<\/h2>\n<h3>Route 3<\/h3>\n<p>Starting at Dresco Town\u2019s PokeCenter, follow these steps to obtain the Deep Sea Scale:<\/p>\n<p><strong>Step 1:<\/strong> Head to the northern end of the town and use the two bridges here to reach Route 3.<\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2025\/01\/01-pokemon-unbound-path-to-bridge-leading-to-route-3.jpg\" alt=\"Path to bridge leading to Route 3 \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Path to bridge leading to Route 3<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p><strong>Step 2:<\/strong> Go down the stairs and walk over to the eastern end of the shore, next to the wooden sign.<\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2025\/01\/02-pokemon-unbound-path-to-eastern-end-of-the-shore.jpg\" alt=\"Path to eastern end of the shore \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Path to eastern end of the shore<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p><strong>Step 3:<\/strong> Use Surf to reach the small piece of land towards the south.<\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2025\/01\/03-pokemon-unbound-path-to-the-piece-of-land-containing-the-deep-sea-scale.jpg\" alt=\"Path to the piece of land containing the Deep Sea Scale \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Path to the piece of land containing the Deep Sea Scale<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p><strong>Step 4:<\/strong> The Deep Sea Scale is hidden in the sand here.<\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2025\/01\/04-pokemon-unbound-exact-location-of-the-deep-sea-scale.jpg\" alt=\"Exact location of the Deep Sea Scale \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Exact location of the Deep Sea Scale<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<h2>Repeatable Methods<\/h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\">\n<table class=\"table grey left\" style=\"min-width:550px;\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Location<\/th>\n<th>Method<\/th>\n<th>Screenshot<\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<\/thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Battle Frontier<\/strong> &#8211; Exchange Service Counter<\/td>\n<td>Exchange for 32 Battle Points (BP)<\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2025\/01\/05-pokemon-unbound-battle-frontier-exchange-service-counter.jpg\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Pokemon Encounters<\/strong> &#8211; (Route 14, Route 16, Route 17, Thundercap Mt., Ruins of Void)<\/td>\n<td>Held by wild Chinchou (5% chance)<\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2025\/01\/06-pokemon-unbound-pokemon-encounters-route-14-route-16-route-17-thundercap-mt-ruins-of-void.jpg\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Pokemon Encounters<\/strong> &#8211; (Route 14, Route 16, Route 17, Thundercap Mt., Ruins of Void)<\/td>\n<td>Held by wild Lanturn (5% chance)<\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2025\/01\/07-pokemon-unbound-pokemon-encounters-route-14-route-16-route-17-thundercap-mt-ruins-of-void-2.jpg\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Pokemon Encounters<\/strong> &#8211; (Victory Road)<\/td>\n<td>Held by wild Basculin (Blue-Striped, 5% chance)<\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2025\/01\/08-pokemon-unbound-pokemon-encounters-victory-road.jpg\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Pokemon Encounters<\/strong> &#8211; (Ruins of Void)<\/td>\n<td>Held by wild Relicanth (5% chance)<\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2025\/01\/09-pokemon-unbound-pokemon-encounters-ruins-of-void.jpg\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<\/div>\n<h2>Uses<\/h2>\n<p>There is only one Pokemon that can evolve using a Deep Sea Scale in Pokemon Unbound.<\/p>\n<table class=\"table grey center even-2col\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Use a Deep Sea Scale on<\/th>\n<th>To evolve into<\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<\/thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/pokemon\/clamperl\/\">Clamperl<\/a><\/td>\n<td><a href=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/pokemon\/gorebyss\/\">Gorebyss<\/a><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n\n        <a href=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/items\/evolution-items\/\" class=\"parent-page-card\">\n            <picture class=\"card-img\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/08\/evolutionary-items.jpg\" class=\"attachment-full size-full wp-post-image\" alt=\"\" \/>\t\t\t\t            <\/picture>\n            <span class=\"card-info\">\n                <span class=\"card-info__caption\">Back to:<\/span>\n                <strong class=\"wiki-title\">Evolution Items<\/strong>\n            <\/span>\n        <\/a>\n\n\t\t\n","protected":false},"featured_media":4575,"parent":1712,"menu_order":1,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_acf_changed":false},"categories":[13],"class_list":["post-4574","wiki","type-wiki","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-items"],"acf":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/wiki\/4574","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/wiki"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/wiki"}],"up":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/wiki\/1712"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/4575"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=4574"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/u